  "body": "Hi,\n\nI have read https://facebook.github.io/react-native/docs/listview.html#content\nIt helps a lot but the example: \n\n```\n_genRows: function(pressData: {[key: number]: boolean}): Array<string> {\n    var dataBlob = [];\n    for (var ii = 0; ii < 100; ii++) {\n      var pressedText = pressData[ii] ? ' (pressed)' : '';\n      dataBlob.push('Row ' + ii + pressedText);\n    }\n    return dataBlob;\n  },\n\n  _pressRow: function(rowID: number) {\n    this._pressData[rowID] = !this._pressData[rowID];\n    this.setState({dataSource: this.state.dataSource.cloneWithRows(\n      this._genRows(this._pressData)\n    )});\n  },\n```\n\nre-render all the other rows at the same time. I am wondering if there is a good way to only re-draw the row I press?\n\nThanks.\n",
